{
  "texts": [
    "As shown in Figure 4, using DNN architecture in predictive models has produced a high accuracy of above 70% and up to 97.5%, and on average 85.89%, except for Ángel Casado Hidalgo et al (2021) which has achieved about 67.2%, that because the model has used a limited dataset from LMS whereas the DL predictive models need for a massive dataset to perform well.",
    "This will not be available for all VLEs, particularly when working on early predictions.",
    "5.1.2 CNNs Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) have demonstrated outstanding performance in predictive modeling as in Akour et al (2020); Begum and Padmannavar (2022); Kavipriya and Sengaliappan (2021); Poudyal et al (2022); Zhang et al (2023).",
    "Two CNN architectures have been used, 1D CNN and 2D CNN, which showed remarkable accuracy above 83.2% and up to 99%, respectively, and an average of 91.84% (see Figure 5).",
    "Therefore, CNNs can be used to analyze student performance data as a sequence, where each data point corresponds to a time step."
  ]
}